Part-timeDesired: Basic Computer SkillsSales ExperienceAre you a talented professional who excels at personalized service, enjoys getting involved in your communities and have a desire to work for one of the Best Places to Work on the Central Coast?

Montecito Bank & Trust is seeking a professional and customer service oriented part-time (30 hours per week) Personal Banker I to join the team in our Westlake Village Branch. This position will primarily service our customers variety of over the counter cash and negotiable transactions.

This is an exciting opportunity for someone who is eager to develop customer relationships and deliver valuable banking products and services to all customers, clients representatives and bank associates and provide a world class experience to all.

Responsibilities will include:
Handling a variety of cash and negotiable transactions accurately and efficiently;
Offering information on bank products and services to benefit the customer and enhancing their relationship;
Accurately operating network of computers/software and other equipment necessary to open new accounts, maintenance required for existing accounts, and handle financial transactions;
Assisting in the acquisition of consumer and small business loan relationships; accepting consumer and small business loan applications and closes loans as directed by management;
Cross-selling and referring to other lines of business.
Education & Experience:
High school diploma or equivalent required; some college preferred;
Must have a minimum 6 months point of sales experience;
Previous teller experience preferred.
Skills:
Ability to accurately handle large amounts of currency;
Strong sales skills;
Strong Math aptitude;
Excellent communication and listening skills;
Good judgment and decision making abilities;
Computer literate in a Windows based environment.
